  "ciliary_role": "Recruitment and stabilisation of CP110 to centrosomes. Both CP110 and CEP97 complexes regulate basal body function, centrosome functions and inhibit cilia assembly (17719545). Loss of CEP97 causes premature cilia formation or abnormal centriole elongation (30375385). CEP97 ubiquitylation and degradation play a key role in the removal of the CEP97–CP110 complex from the mother centriole for initiating ciliary axoneme extension (30404837).",
